      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For the tea tree oil, apply a very thin layer—think barely a sheen, not a thick coat—to avoid burning, about half a drop per square centimeter of the affected area. You can absolutely layer them; apply the antibiotic ointment first, let it sink in for five minutes, and then gently dab the diluted tea tree oil over the top. This combination is a powerhouse; it's going to cleanse and heal that spot faster than you think!",
